Featured Music- Hills and Valleys- Tauren Wells More
Michigan native Tauren Wells started his music career at Indiana Bible College, forming the group Royal Tailor with a trio of classmate friends. From their two albums, the group earned two Grammy nominations, and won the Dove Award for New Artist of the Year. However, when life on the road began to take it's toll on the group, Tauren persevered, and launched his solo career with Essential Records. 
After landing a key spot in the multi-million-view Dude Perfect series with his "Undefeated" KB collaboration, Wells returns with a full length collection of electrifying pop-rock anthems and heartfelt songs of faith.  Read More

Featured Artist- Nichole Nordeman More
Over the course of her career, Nichole Nordeman's writings and musicianship have continually blessed to the Christian community with life wisdom, spiritual encouragement, poetic beauty, and vibrant reminders of God's grace. Following her early days as a church pianist in hometown Colorado Springs, Nicole gained recognition at a GMA sponsored music contest, captivating audiences with her original music and lyrical gifts. Since her breakout debut, she's written hits for other artists and recorded her own music, penned the powerful "Music Inspired By The Story" collection, and published her first book, becoming a wife and mother along the way... Read More

